  248. ‌type function_kind = Curried | Tupled

  250. ‌type let_kind = Strict | Alias | StrictOpt
  251. (* Meaning of kinds for let x = e in e':
  252.     Strict: e may have side-effects; always evaluate e first
  253.       (If e is a simple expression, e.g. a variable or constant,
  254.        we may still substitute e'[x/e].)
  255.     Alias: e is pure, we can substitute e'[x/e] if x has 0 or 1 occurrences
  256.       in e'
  257.     StrictOpt: e does not have side-effects, but depend on the store;
  258.       we can discard e if x does not appear in e'
  259. *)

  261. ‌type meth_kind = Self | Public | Cached

  343. ‌type program =
  344.   { module_ident : Ident.t;
  345.     main_module_block_size : int;
  346.     required_globals : Ident.Set.t;    (* Modules whose initializer side effects
  347.                                           must occur before [code]. *)
  348.     code : lambda }
  349. (* Lambda code for the middle-end.
  350.    * In the closure case the code is a sequence of assignments to a
  351.      preallocated block of size [main_module_block_size] using
  352.      (Setfield(Getglobal(module_ident))). The size is used to preallocate
  353.      the block.
  354.    * In the flambda case the code is an expression returning a block
  355.      value of size [main_module_block_size]. The size is used to build
  356.      the module root as an initialize_symbol
  357.      Initialize_symbol(module_name, 0,
  358.        [getfield 0; ...; getfield (main_module_block_size - 1)])
  359. *)

  410. ‌val subst:
  411.   (Ident.t -> Types.value_description -> Env.t -> Env.t) ->
  412.   ?freshen_bound_variables:bool ->
  413.   lambda Ident.Map.t -> lambda -> lambda
  414. (** [subst update_env ?freshen_bound_variables s lt]
  415.     applies a substitution [s] to the lambda-term [lt].

  417.     Assumes that the image of the substitution is out of reach
  418.     of the bound variables of the lambda-term (no capture).

  420.     [update_env] is used to refresh the environment contained in debug
  421.     events.

  423.     [freshen_bound_variables], which defaults to [false], freshens
  424.     the bound variables within [lt].
  425. *)
